The paper deals with action recognition in videos, which is a problem in computer vision (cs.CV). The proposed approach involves the use of generative adversarial networks (GANs) for synthesizing video features, which is a technique commonly used in machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also involves the use of natural language processing techniques for text-based classification of action categories, which falls under the category of computational linguistics (cs.CL). Finally, the paper involves the use of multimedia data (videos) and their analysis, which falls under the category of multimedia (cs.MM).
